post_text:
Student Cohorts for Phase I of 2020-21 Academic Year

• Cohort A (Students whose last name begins with A-L): Students assigned to Cohort A will attend in-person classes on Mondays and Thursdays and participate in remote instruction on Tuesdays and Fridays.
• Cohort B (Students whose last name begins with M-Z): Students assigned to Cohort B will attend in-person classes on Tuesdays and Fridays and participate in remote instruction on Mondays and Thursdays.
• All Students: On Wednesdays, all students will participate in remote instruction. This remote instruction will allow for teachers and students to engage in synchronous learning activities, and provide the district an opportunity to clean all buildings.

This is a reminder that the school district is offering meals for free and reduced eligible recipients. The district will continue to use a “Grab and Go” program.

Start Monday, March 30th, to better serve the community Sixteenth Avenue eligible students can pick-up their meals at Sixteenth Avenue School front parking lot side door from 10-11am Monday to Friday. Gilbert and Gantner eligible students can continue to pick-up their meals between 11am to 12 noon Monday to Friday and middle school and high school students from 12 noon to 1pm at the High School cafeteria.

Thank you and be safe.

post_text:
The forecast is calling for inclement weather during the day tomorrow. However, due to the uncertainty of the forecast, we will not be making any decisions this evening. We will monitor the weather tonight and tomorrow morning and make a decision in the morning.

However, please be prepared should we need to call a school closing or early dismissal. If we decide to close schools or dismiss early, a message will go out early tomorrow morning informing all parents. If you do not receive a notification (phone call or email), schools will follow a regular full day schedule.

Thank you for your understanding and have a good evening.

Reminders for the Week of November 4-6, 2019

1. On Monday, November 4th, all high school students are invited to the annual College Fair held by the Guidance Department. This program will run from 6:30pm-8:00pm in the Middle School Multi-Purpose Room.

2. On Tuesday, November 5th, the Elmwood Park school district will be closed for student’s due to Election Day and a Professional Development Day.

3. On Thursday, November 7th and Friday, November 8th, the Elmwood Park school district will be closed due to the NJEA Teacher's Convention.

4. To provide an opportunity for students to spend more time with their families, there will be no homework assigned during the days of 11/7/19 - 11/10/19 (only long-term assignments will have been assigned).

Thank you.

Due to the impending forecast of snow and the need for additional cleanup time the Elmwood Park Public Schools will have a delayed opening Monday, March 4th. Students should report to the high school and middle school at 10:00am and the elementary schools at 10:45am. There will be no half day pre-k programs tomorrow.

However, we will reassess road and school conditions in the morning and make a decision regarding a possible school closing. A school closing may be necessary due to significant accumulations. Either way, parents will receive notification tomorrow morning to confirm either a delayed opening or school closing.

Thank you for your understanding and have a good evening.

post_text: As you know, a massive fire destroyed the landmark Marcal Paper Factory on Wednesday evening. I want to take a moment to thank all first responders who were involved in fighting the fire. The bravery that was displayed is yet another reason why I’m proud to be a part of Elmwood Park.
text: As you know, a massive fire destroyed the landmark Marcal Paper Factory on Wednesday evening. I want to take a moment to thank all first responders who were involved in fighting the fire. The bravery that was displayed is yet another reason why I’m proud to be a part of Elmwood Park.

post_text:
First, I would like to take this opportunity to personally thank the first responders, all of those in the community and surrounding areas that have come to support Elmwood Park in its time of crisis. Thankfully there were no injuries reported and everyone returned home safely.

Due to the fire at Marcal last night and its effect on the River Road traffic pattern, the Elmwood Park Public Schools will have a delayed opening Friday, February 1st. Please be mindful of the change in the flow of traffic as River Road will be closed between Summit Ave and Market Street. Please take alternate routes.

Tomorrow students should report to the high school and middle school at 10:00am and the elementary schools at 10:45am. There will be no half-day pre-k programs tomorrow.

Thank you and please be safe when you are traveling through the town.

On the 11th hour of the 11th day of the 11th month of 1918 World War I officially ended. In 1919 President Wilson proclaimed the date to be Armistice Day and in 1938 the name was changed to Veteran’s Day. Today marks the 100th anniversary of the end of World War I.
Please use November 11th to remember the sacrifice this nation’s service men and women have made and thank them for protecting our freedoms.
